cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a threat to network infrastructure and proposes a framework for early detection of the attack. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Computer Security (cs.CR) and Network Infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also proposes the use of deep learning methods for attack detection, which falls under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of monitoring traffic at potential decoy servers, which relates to the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
